description.narrative:
The Georgian Farmers’ Association (GFA) has applied to the Embassy of Sweden for pre-core support with the funding of 1 633 000 SEK to implement the following:

1) Perform an organizational assessment; 
2) Develop a new 5 year strategic plan for the years 2020 - 2024; 
3) Follow up and implement the recommendations of the review of internal management and control systems conducted by the KPMG Georgia LLC in July 2019. 

The contribution aims at improving the organizational capacity, enhance the internal management and control systems and sustainable strategic development of GFA. 

The total amount of the pre-core support  is 1 633 000 SEK for the period 1 November 2019 - 30 June  2020, followed with a close dialogue on core-support for implementation of the new strategy later in 2020.
